The following article is from the Earth's Youth Almanac, the author of Diqing

The alternative to being young

According to the latest information from the Ministry of Health, as of noon on March 16,14,991 cases of new coronary pneumonia had been confirmed in Iran, of which 4,996 had recovered and 853 had died.

In order to curb the development of the epidemic and detect suspected cases of infection as soon as possible, Iran announced earlier this month the launch of a national mobilization plan, will be sent to all parts of the country 300,000 medical team door-to-door to check the epidemic.

As of March 15, Iran's national mobilization plan had completed the screening of 10 million people, Deputy Health Minister Ali Reza Recy said, according to the Islamic Republic News Agency. After screening, 210,000 people were found to have at least one suspected symptom.

From March 10 to 15 local time, Phoenix satellite TV correspondent Li Rui took to the streets of Tehran to ask local people's views on the epidemic.
